track_notes: A classic climb in the Rockies with a long and technical quartzite ridge. There are a few sections of the climb rated as 5.3/5.4, but our route has one pitch of 5.5. Start from the Taylor Lake parking lot and hike along the well-maintained trail up to Taylor Lake. From here, follow the trail to OBrien Lake and make a detour into the forest at the cairn just after the first bridge. Bushwhack to a larch meadow and scramble up to the ridge. The ridge involves 3rd and 4th class scrambling up some good quartzite. There is some mudstone, but never on challenging sections. We pitched out two sections: one with a larger slab wall and another technical step which leads to the 5.5 move above. We used 50m ropes although a 60m rope would be better. For protection, we brought a standard rack of nuts and a single set of cams from #0.5 to #3. Once you reach the summit, descent via the scrambling route to the SE col. From the SE col, hike through OBrien Lake back to the Taylor Lake trail.
track_title: Mount Bell NE Ridge Climb and SE Col Descent
